<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="prepare-v">prepare <strong><em>v</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /prɪ'peə(r)/    美 /prɪ'per/  </p>
<p>vt &amp; vi</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>使做好准备；把...准备好</strong></h4>
<p>to make sth or sb ready to be used or to do sth：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>prepare dinner
准备晚餐</p></div>

<ul>
<li>prepare sth / sb for sb / sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>A hotel room is being prepared for the guest.
正在为这位客人准备一间旅馆客房。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The function of education is to prepare us for life.
教育的作用是让我们对生活有所准备。</p><footer>2011 安徽</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>(使自己) 有准备</strong></h4>
<p>to make yourself ready to do sth or for sth that you expect to happen：</p>
<ul>
<li>prepare for sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Hope for the best, and prepare for the worst.
抱最好的希望，做最坏的打算。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The lectures help students prepare for college mathematics.
这些课程有助于学生为大学数学做好准备。</p><footer>2012 北京改</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>prepare oneself (for sth):</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I closed my eyes and prepared myself for his burst of anger.
我闭上眼睛做好了准备，等他大发雷霆。</p><footer>2013 陕西</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>prepare (oneself) to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Buy the album, and prepare to be amazed.
买下这张专辑，准备好感受惊喜吧。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The troops prepared themselves to go into battle.
部队准备开赴战场。</p></div></div>